CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 15, 1941, pg. 5, reads: "Listening for Her Master's Voice - Pretty Eunice Walker of 3358 Webster avenue, hasn't as yet found her Valentine, but she isn't giving up. Pictured above, Eunice resorts to the air lanes in her search for Dan Cupid, who couldn't help but look twice if he saw her.  Eunice is a student at Herron Hill Junior High School. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Eunice Walker wearing plaid dress and seated on dark armchair with radio in background, in her home at 3358 Webster Avenue, Hill District
